The paper deals with manifold learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of determinantal point processes, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS) for diverse sampling. The paper proposes a new method for landmark selection, which involves assigning local covariance matrices to each landmark, which is a technique commonly used in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the performance improvement of the proposed method, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
